<h2>Basic Example</h2>

<p>First up, let's show off a very basic example of <code>ivy-tabs</code> in action. Here we have some tabs and panels defined directly in the template. We've bound the active selection to a <code>basicSelection</code> property, whose value is currently <code>{{basicSelection}}</code>.</p>

<div class="example">
  {{#ivy-tabs selection=basicSelection as |tabs|}}
    {{#tabs.tablist class="nav nav-tabs" tagName="ul" as |tablist|}}
      <li class="{{if (eq basicSelection "A") "active"}}" role="presentation">
        {{#tablist.tab "A" on-select=(action (mut basicSelection))}}Tab A{{/tablist.tab}}
      </li>
      <li class="{{if (eq basicSelection "B") "active"}}" role="presentation">
        {{#tablist.tab "B" on-select=(action (mut basicSelection))}}Tab B{{/tablist.tab}}
      </li>
      <li class="{{if (eq basicSelection "C") "active"}}" role="presentation">
        {{#tablist.tab "C" on-select=(action (mut basicSelection))}}Tab C{{/tablist.tab}}
