<h2>Query Parameters</h2>

<p>Like in the basic example above, we've bound the selection to a property. This time, we've called it <code>querySelection</code>, and its current value is <code>{{querySelection}}</code>. We've also told Ember to treat it as a query parameter, aliased to <code>tab</code>. Notice how the URL changes when you select a new tab? Now try refreshing the page. Neat, huh?</p>

